  "narrative": "DRIVER\nNZD leads H4 CSM at 100 with the sharpest D1-H4 divergence in the dataset (100 vs 40), confirming the H4 regime shift to risk-on low is accelerating fastest in NZD as US-Iran diplomatic progress and DXY weakness at 99.24 collapse safe-haven demand. NZDUSD and NZDJPY are the cleanest expressions, with AUD close behind at H4 88 making AUDNZD a compression pair and AUDJPY a secondary long. CHF D1-H4 divergence (100 vs 77) flags fading safe-haven bid that undermines USDCHF short narratives despite broad USD weakness.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: None\nFading: None\n\nWATCH\nUS consumer sentiment data release hits USDCAD directly given CAD H4 CSM accelerating to 44 from D1 21, a further soft print confirms USD selling extends the USDCAD downtrend toward key support. JPY resilience narrative tests at 159.00 USDJPY resistance, a rejection there with JPY H4 CSM at 55 triggers GBPJPY long unwind. Gold at 4523 holding despite risk-on confirms inflation repricing, a break above 4530 pressures XAUUSD shorts and reinforces NZDUSD upside continuation.",
